                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d912">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/10835: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-20T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 20, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>916. My 908, May 19. Foreign Minister has informed Hugessen and myself that as a
                    measure of good will he has directed appropriate Turk authorities that exports
                    to Axis of strategic materials listed in British and American notes of April 14
                    are to be immediately reduced to 55 percent of quantities exported in 1943.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
